also HUGE tip - iirc rocksdb is a dependency. if you just install librocksdb with the os's package manager, and set the env var `ROCKSDB_LIB_DIR` to point to the directory of librocksdb so it doesn't have to build it from scratch, it will speed up compile time by a *very* noticeable amount lmaaooo.
on ubuntu lts 24 on an x86 machine it should be `ROCKSDB_LIB_DIR=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/` iirc.
Sweet thanks!!

the package should be called `librocksdb-dev` - so:
`sudo apt-get install librocksdb-dev`
will likely be called something different on i.e. AUR if ur on arch.

if you're on macos (with an m-series chip):
```
brew install rocksdb
```
will install librocks db, the env var should be set to:
```
